==== Component 1: Cross-Sectional Metabolic-Immune Comparison (n=80)

Compare ME/CFS patients with vs.\ without metabolic syndrome (MS) on inflammatory markers and neuroinflammatory burden.
*Participants:*
    - n=40 ME/CFS without metabolic syndrome
    - n=40 ME/CFS with metabolic syndrome (modified NCEP criteria)
*Outcomes:*
    - Inflammatory marker profiles (IL-6, TNF-$alpha$, IL-1$beta$, CRP)
    - TSPO-PET signal (subset, n=10 per group)
    - Cognitive function (Montreal Cognitive Assessment)
    - Functional capacity (Bell scale)

